  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Give girls in domestic work a safe place in Peru</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">La Casa de Panchita exists because girls as young as 9 from the poverty of the Andes and shantytowns are forced to work cleaning, cooking and watching children in other people&apos;s homes. They are years behind in their schooling and often doomed to work in domestic service their entire life. Through workshops, psychological counseling, school support and recreational  and cultural field-trips, at La Casa de Panchita we help these girls and adolescents pursue a better and dignified life.</narrative>
  </description>
